[00:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'The QuadraF kit is your key to the spatial wireless world. With four full duplex antennas and a built-in [music] Raspberry Pi, it runs hundreds of software defined radio applications. Add your phone and the mobile battery'

[00:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'pack, and you have an instant augmented reality window into the wireless signals around you. Observe how radio signals propagate and reflect off of surfaces. Frequency is represented by color,'

[00:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'giving you real-time insight into Wi-Fi channel activity. See who is hogging the airwaves or phoning home. Hunt transmitters down and understand'

[00:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'how devices connect and interact. Wi-Fi signals pass right through walls. When you can see radio waves, you\'ll be'

[00:59] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'surprised what you can discover. QuadraF runs GNU Radio directly on board, which you can access with your web browser along with a helpful control GUI. You can create high-speed point-to-point links with automatic'

[01:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'beamforming, transmitting between two QuadraFs over long distances, or even create mesh MIMO networks. The QuadraF lets robots communicate, too. They can see and navigate around devices'

[01:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and access points. Mounting on a quadcopter, you can take to the skies and measure RF from above. Of course, quadcopters generate their'

[01:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'own wireless signals, too. You can track multiple simultaneously. Or pick one, lock on,'

[01:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and decode its camera feed live on your phone using one of the many onboard apps. As an all digital software defined radio with four coherent transmitters and four'

[02:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'receivers, [music] Quadre F is bounded only by your imagination.'
